HEADWORD: Homoptera
<hw>Ho*mop"te*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ the same, like + <?/ wing.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
suborder of Hemiptera, in which both pairs of wings are similar in
texture, and do not overlap when folded, as in the cicada. See
<er>Hemiptera</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homopteran</ent>⟦br⟧
